Software for Little Magic Boxes (stay tuned).

Home https://github.com/networkimprov/elembe

--- Summary ---

A personal-area network (i.e. WiFi Direct or Bluetooth) browser-based app with desktop integration.

--- Requirements ---

Linux

Node.js http://github.com/ry/node

Node modules:
  node-inotify https://github.com/c4milo/node-inotify
  node-sqlite https://github.com/networkimprov/node-sqlite
  uuidjs https://github.com/weaver/uuidjs
  gm https://github.com/aheckmann/gm
  socket.io-node https://github.com/LearnBoost/Socket.IO-node
  websocket.MQ client https://github.com/networkimprov/websocket.MQ

Libraries & Tools:
  SQLite http://sqlite.org/
  libuuid 
  Graphicsmagick http://graphicsmagick.org/
  Xdelta3 http://xdelta.org/
  Socket.IO (in elembe/socket.io/) https://github.com/LearnBoost/Socket.IO

Samba file server http://samba.org/
  configure a share [sqltest] path = elembe/sqltest/

On Clients:

Firefox (currently) http://mozilla.org/

AppLaunch Firefox extension https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/240637/

--- Startup ---

$ node elembe.js autogen # first time only
$ node elembe.js
Point Firefox to http://yourhost:8000/

